cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.CE, cs.CG, cs.ME 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper presents a reformulation of the finite strain theory using the Tangential Differential Calculus (TDC), which involves mathematical concepts and equations. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the application of the proposed finite strain theory to numerical methods, such as the Surface FEM and Trace FEM, and presents numerical results. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper deals with the modeling and simulation of physical systems, such as ropes, membranes, and three-dimensional continua, using a unified finite strain theory. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper discusses the representation of geometries using parametrized and implicit forms, and how the proposed formulation is more general than classical ones. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper deals with the modeling and simulation of mechanical systems, such as ropes and membranes, using a unified finite strain theory.
